VEager to add a luxury chain to its portfolio, Marriott International announced yesterday that it had agreed to acquire about 49 percent of the Ritz-Carlton Hotel Company. Marriott is not buying any of the Ritz hotels, which are mostly franchised, only the right to manage them. The proposed acquisition, which also includes several minority partners, is scheduled to close this spring, and Marriott could later acquire the rest of the company.
