VWhen the Marriott hotel chain agreed in February to pay more than $400 million to settle a series of lawsuits brought by disgruntled investors in its hotels, lawyers on both sides were quick to praise the deal. And no wonder. The settlement offers the chance to end a messy chapter in the corporate histories of Marriott International and Host Marriott, two closely related companies that manage and own Marriott hotels. And for the Houston trial lawyers who led the charge against Marriott, the deal provides roughly $70 million without the risk of a trial.
