VThe Marriott Corporation said yesterday that it had split in two, completing its contentious plan to separate its hotel management business from its real estate properties. Shareholders received one share of Marriott International Inc., a new lodging and services managment company, for each share they owned in the Marriott Corporation. The parent company is being renamed Host Marriott. The plan had first been announced a year ago but ran into strong opposition from bondholders since $3 billion of the company's debts were left at Host Marriott, raising the risks on the bonds. They fell 30 percent after the announcement. The company then modified the plan in March, redistributing to Marriott International $450 million of the debt and coming up with a new exchange offer that eventually appeased bondholders.
