VMARRIOTT INTERNATIONAL INC., Bethesda, Md., the largest U.S. hotel chain, sold its Waikiki Beach Marriott Resort for about $130 million in cash to a group led by CNL Hospitality Corp., a real estate developer. Marriott said it would hold a minority stake in the resort and continue to operate it under a long-term agreement.
