VHospitality Properties Trust announced yesterday that it had acquired four hotels from Marriott International for $101.5 million and would lease its 35 Marriott-managed hotels to a new taxable subsidiary. Hospitality, based in Newton, Mass., bought a 356-room Marriott in Kauai, Hawaii; a 295-room Courtyard by Marriott in Emeryville, Calif.; a 135-room TownePlace Suites hotel and the 114-room SpringHill Suites hotel in Renton, Wash. Marriott will manage all 35 hotels through 2019, Hospitality said. Hospitality will lease the 35 hotels to a new taxable subsidiary, taking advantage of this year's REIT Modernization Act, under which real estate trusts that own hotels no longer have to lease properties to outside managers. The hotels were previously leased to Marriott. Hospitality now owns 228 hotels in 37 states.
