VTHE daunting challenges that still confront the Interpublic Group of Companies in New York as it struggles to effect a turnaround were underlined yesterday in red ink -- pots of red ink. Interpublic reported a wider third-quarter loss, the biggest for any quarter in two years, on higher costs for layoffs, an accelerated revamping, write-offs for troubled operations and the potential settlement of shareholder lawsuits.
