VMarriott International said yesterday that it had agreed to sell eight hotels in California, New Jersey, Pennsylvania and Virginia for $181 million to the CNL Hospitality Corporation, part of the CNL Financial Group. The sale includes one Residence Inn, three Courtyard by Marriott hotels, three SpringHill Suites hotels and one TownePlace Suites hotel. Marriott, based in Bethesda, Md., will continue to operate the hotels under long-term management agreements with a CNL Hospitality affiliate. Two of the hotels, one in Oakland, Calif., and one in Richmond, Va., have already been sold, a Marriott spokesman said.
