VMEDICAL ACTION INDUSTRIES, Hauppauge, N.Y., a maker of disposable medical and surgical products, said it had completed the purchase of MD Industries, Northbrook, Ill., a maker of packaging and collection systems for biohazard and chemotherapy waste. Terms were not disclosed. XEROX CORP., Stamford, Conn., the copier maker, said it had completed the renegotiation of its revolving credit line by repaying $2.8 billion and getting an extension of the maturity date for the remaining $4.2 billion.
